Title says it - what are some really creative, outside-the-box climbers this year?
Ones I’ve seen that are really different / unique:
4907 Thunderstamps jump climb
2481 Roboteers driving up the truss
2405 Techno Trojans with their dorito climber

I’m sure there are many other unique ones…

The skip-high-bar climbers are pretty out-of-the-box IMO.

125 and 3310 have different designs that leverage off the high bar to swing hooks up to traversal.

1690, 254, 2337 and maybe others don’t interact with the high bar at all and instead leverage off the truss.

I’m going to put a vote in for 341. Lots of teams have been doing the, “Windmill,” climb, but I have yet to see another team with such a cool latching mechanism as them. They built a gear into the finger and rotate the entire latch around the bar so there is no way for them to fall off if the sequence is correct.

Check it out here:

Here is a quick snapshot:

I don’t feel like we have a super creative climber but we did get the creativity award at both of our competitions. It uses a modified climber in a box, different hooks rotation at the bottom and a 2nd wench and spring to control the rotation. This allows us to reliably control our center of gravity and decrease the swinging. (Team 5492) allthough some of that award had to do with our fold out electrical box.

Our Blue Alliance photo has the truss reaction bar, but we couldn’t get our claws to latch fully, so we switched, partially inspired by 3310 as well I believe. Instead we use fiberglass poles that bend on the high rung and react us into the right angle to connect with our claws.
